Obviously this needs to be studied by science, I haven&#39;t seen anyone argue differently.  ITC in general has been attacked since Jurgenson.  When Konstantin Raudive went into the shielded control room of Pye Studios and recorded EVP&#39;s, it still wasn&#39;t good enough for &quot;science.&quot;

Fact is, as I alluded to earlier in the post you so graciously &quot;skimmed,&quot; science is not studying this.  Real two way communication through frequency sweeping radio has only come to light less than nine years ago.  

What scientists do you think would study this?  What lab would take on the Ghost Boxes as a project?  The answer: none.  Why?  Because there is no way a project like this could get funding.  Also, if any reputed lab did study this and found out that there might be something to it, and then published about it, any scientists involved with that lab would be black listed from future projects just do to the incendiary nature of exploring the paranormal.  

So it is up to independent people to work on this stuff right now, which, as stated earlier, is in its absolute infancy as an ITC device.  The fact is that there are many people who use these boxes and if they do it at all seriously, then they get results...some of which are indicative of some intelligence trying to communicate with us.

Association Transcommunication (Formerly AA-EVP) has recently embarked upon a study of ghost boxes, but the results are not yet available because they are being examined and the results interpreted.  If they post something positive (white papers are always available on their site), would that constitute proof for you?  These guys are going to be the closest thing to unbiased research that you will find in the field and their reputation is impeccable.

http://atransc.org/journal/radiosweep_study.htm

For the rest of us, we do not have labs, nor the equipment to do the rigorous science you call for to find the proof.  Most of us have no idea how electronics, physics, or energy waves work.  We accept that, we just know that our boxes work.  This is the same as turning on a light bulb...we don&#39;t know diddly about how electrons fire or electricity is generated, but I&#39;ll be damned if there isn&#39;t a light while I&#39;m typing this and it works.  

Would you please answer a two-part question for my own edification?

What would you consider proof, and how can evidential proof be presented to you so it will not be in question? 

And yes, you figured out the big secret: we are a cult.  Too bad you won&#39;t drink the Kool-Aid with us.

Tim W.

